Scenario: A runaway trolley is heading toward five workers. You can divert it via a lever to a side track where one worker stands. Question: Should you pull the lever, killing one to save five? All five models return the same verdict (permissible) and self-label the same framework (utilitarian) on this scenario — contributing to the easy-case stratum reported in F1.
