The action minimizes overall harm by sacrificing one life to save five, which produces the greatest good for the greatest number. Choosing not to act would result in a greater loss of life, making intervention the morally preferable choice. (Principle: An action is morally right if it maximizes overall utility and minimizes suffering.)
- Qwen3.5-397B verdict: permissible, framework: utilitarian, conf: 4/5
